cleaningdescription:
• Cleaning fees are always refunded if the guest did not check-in.

• The %@ service fee is refundable if the guest cancels before the trip starts. If a guest books a reservation that overlaps with any part of an existing reservation, we won’t refund the %@ service fee if they decide to cancel.

•Accommodation fees the total nightly rate you're charged) are refundable in certain circumstances as outlined below.

• If there is a complaint from either party, notice must be given to %@ within 24 hours of check-in.

• %@ will mediate when necessary, and has the final say in all disputes.

• A reservation is officially canceled when the guest clicks the cancellation button on the cancellation confirmation page, which they can find in Dashboard > Your Trips > Cancel. 

• Cancellation policies may be superseded by the Guest Refund Policy, extenuating circumstances, or cancellations by %@ for any other reason permitted under the Terms of Service. Please review these exceptions. 

• Applicable taxes will be retained and remitted.

lawtitle: Take a moment to review your local laws. We want to make sure you've got everything you need to get off to a great start.
lawdes:
Please educate yourself about the laws in your jurisdiction before listing your space.

Most cities have rules covering home sharing, and the specific codes and ordinances can appear in many places (such as zoning, building, licensing or tax codes). In most places, you must register, get a permit, or obtain a license before you list your property or accept guests. You may also be responsible for collecting and remitting certain taxes. In some places, short-term rentals could be prohibited altogether.

Since you are responsible for your own decision to list or book, you should get comfortable with the applicable rules before listing on %@. To get you started, we offer some helpful resources under “Your City Laws.” 

By accepting our Terms of Service and listing your space, you certify that you will follow applicable laws and regulations.

ModeratePolicy: For a full refund of accommodation fees, cancellation must be made five full days prior to listing’s local check-in time (or 3:00 PM if not specified) on the day of check-in. For example, if check-in is on Friday, cancel by the previous Sunday before check-in time.
StrictPolicy: For a 50% refund of accommodation fees, cancellation must be made seven full days prior to listing’s local check-in time (or 3:00 PM if not specified) on the day of check-in, otherwise no refund. For example, if check-in is on Friday, cancel by Friday of the previous week before check-in time.
FlexiblePolicy: For a full refund of accommodation fees, cancellation must be made a full 24 hours prior to listing’s local check-in time (or 3:00 PM if not specified) on the day of check-in. For example, if check-in is on Friday, cancel by Thursday of that week before check-in time.
ModerateDescription: If the guest cancels less than 7 days in advance, the nights not spent are not refunded.
StrictDescription: If the guest cancels less than 5 days in advance, the first night is non-refundable but 50% of the accommodation fees for remaining nights will be refunded.
FlexibleDecsription: If the guest cancels less than 24 hours before check-in, the first night is non-refundable.

FlexibleExample: For ex: Say a guest booked a stay and their check-in time is 3:00 PM on June 09th.
FlexiblebeforeDescription: A full refund will be processed if a guest cancels a booking 24 hrs before check-in time.
FlexiblebeforeExample: For ex:  If a guest cancels the booking before 3:00 PM on June 08th, a 100% refund will be processed.
Flexiblecheckindescription: If a guest cancels their booking less than 24 hrs before the check-in time, then the first night of the stay is non-refundable.
FlexiblecheckinExample: For ex:  If a guest cancels the booking after 3:00 PM on June 08th, the first night of the stay is non-refundable, and the rest will be refunded.
Flexiblecheckout: The accommodation fees for the nights not spent will be returned if a guest checks in and decides to leave early.
ModerateDescription1: 100% refund only if canceled 5 days before check-in time.
ModerateExample: For ex: Say a guest booked a stay and their check-in time is 3:00 PM on June 09th.
ModeratebeforeDescription: Only if a guest cancels their reservation 5 days prior to the check-in time will they receive a full refund.
moderatebeforeExample: For ex: If a guest cancels the booking before 3:00 PM on June 04th, a 100% refund will be processed.
Moderatecheckindescription: If a guest cancels their booking less than 5 days before the check-in time, then the first night of the stay is non-refundable. But 50% amount for the rest of the nights will be refunded.
ModeratecheckinExample: For ex: If a guest cancels their reservation after 3:00 PM on June 5, the first night of their stay is non-refundable, and 50% of the remaining nights will be refunded.
Moderatecheckout: 50% of the accommodation fees for the nights not spent will be refunded (24hrs after the cancellation) if a guest checks in and decides to leave early.
StrictDescription1: 50% refund only if canceled 7 days before check-in time.
StrictExample: For ex: Say a guest booked a stay and their check-in time is 3:00 PM on June 09th.
StrictbeforeDescription: Only if a guest cancels their reservation 7 days prior to the check-in time will they receive a 50% refund.
StrictbeforeExample: For ex: If a guest cancels the booking before 3:00 PM on June 2nd, a 50% refund will be processed.
Strictcheckindescription: There will be no refund if a guest cancels their booking less than 7 days before the check-in time.
StrictcheckinExample: For ex: No refund will be given if a guest cancels their reservation after 3:00 PM on June 1st.
Strictcheckout: If a guest checks in and decides to leave early, there will be no refund for the nights not spent.
